Canonical Java decimal-to-binary template

String toBinary(int n) {
    if (n == 0) {
        return "0";
    }

    StringBuilder bits = new StringBuilder();

    while (n > 0) {
        bits.append(n % 2);
        n /= 2;
    }

    return bits.reverse().toString();
}

Also know:
- n % 2 checks odd/even
- n / 10 and n % 10 for digit problems

